b]]<ref name=\"SW\"/>\n*[[Primera Divisi\u00f3n de Argentina|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]]: [[2014 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|2014]], [[2018\u201319 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|2018\u201319]]\n\n;[[Boca Juniors]]<ref name=\"SW\"/>\n*[[Primera Divisi\u00f3n de Argentina|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]]: [[2016\u201317 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|2016\u201317]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120919052025/http://www.racingclub.com.ar/futbol/plantel/jugador/18_centurion Profile] at Racing Club's official website {{in lang|es}} \n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160304055044/http://www.futbolxxi.com/Futbolista.aspx?ID=15085&SEOFutbolista=Centurion+Adrian+Ricardo Argentine Primera statistics] {{in lang|es}}\n\n{{V\u00e9lez Sarsfield squad}}\n<!-- {{Racing Club de Avellaneda squad}} -->\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Centurion, Ricardo}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association football wingers]]\n[[Category:Argentine footballers]]\n[[Category:Argentine expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Racing Club de Avellaneda footballers]]\n[[Category:Genoa C.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:S\u00e3o Paulo FC players]]\n[[Category:Boca Juniors footballers]]\n[[Category:Atl\u00e9tico San Luis footballers]]\n[[Category:Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield footballers]]\n[[Category:Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Serie A players]]\n[[Category:Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A players]]\n[[Category:Liga MX players]]\n[[Category:Argentine expatriate sportspeople in Italy]]\n[[Category:Argentine expatriate sportspeople in Brazil]]\n[[Category:Argentine expatriate sportspeople in Mexico]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Italy]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Brazil]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Mexico]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Ricardo Centuri\u00f3n\n| image          = Ricardo Centuri\u00f3n (2016).jpg\n| image_size     = 200px\n| caption        =  Centuri\u00f3n at the [[S\u00e3o Paulo\u2013Guarulhos International Airport|Airport of S\u00e3o Paulo]] in 2016\n| fullname       = Adri\u00e1n Ricardo Centuri\u00f3n  \n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1993|1|19|df=y}} \n| birth_place    = [[Avellaneda]], Argentina\n| height         = 1.74 m\n| position       = [[Left winger (association football)|Left-winger]]\n| currentclub    = [[Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield|V\u00e9lez Sarsfield]]<br />(on loan from [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing Club]])\n| clubnumber     = \n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing Club]]\n| years1         = 2012\u20132014\n| clubs1         = [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing Club]]\n| caps1          = 41\n| goals1         = 7\n| years2         = 2013\u20132014\n| clubs2         = \u2192 [[Genoa C.F.C.|Genoa]] (loan)\n| caps2          = 12\n| goals2         = 0\n| years3         = 2015\u20132017\n| clubs3         = [[S\u00e3o Paulo FC|S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n| caps3          = 40\n| goals3         = 2\n| years4         = 2016\u20132017\n| clubs4         = \u2192 [[Boca Juniors]] (loan)\n| caps4          = 22\n| goals4         = 8\n| years5         = 2017\n| clubs5         = [[Genoa C.F.C.|Genoa]]\n| caps5          = 3\n| goals5         = 0\n| years6         = 2018\u2013\n| clubs6         = [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing Club]]\n| caps6          = 29\n| goals6         = 10\n| years7         = 2019\n| clubs7         = \u2192 [[Atl\u00e9tico San Luis]] (loan)\n| caps7          = 9\n| goals7         = 0\n| years8         = 2020\u2013\n| clubs8         = \u2192 [[Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield|V\u00e9lez Sarsfield]] (loan)\n| caps8          = 5\n| goals8         = 1\n| nationalyears1 = 2012\u20132013\n| nationalteam1  = [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina U20]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 5\n| nationalgoals1 = 2\n| nationalyears2 = 2018\n| nationalteam2  = [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]]\n| nationalcaps2  = 0\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| club-update    = 14 March 2020\n| ntupdate       = \n}}\n\n'''Adri\u00e1n Ricardo Centuri\u00f3n''' (born 19 January 1993) is an Argentine professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Left winger|left-winger]] for [[Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield|V\u00e9lez Sarsfield]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Racing Club and loan with Genoa===\nCenturi\u00f3n joined Racing's youth setup at the age of 15 and came through the ranks.<ref name=\"bbc\"/><ref name=\"vivaformica\"/>\n\nOn 19 August 2012, Centuri\u00f3n had a hand in both goals<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=apx5UhnzQpE \"Racing 2-0 Independiente (highlights)\"]. ''YouTube'', 19 August 2012. Retrieved 25 January 2013.</ref> as Racing defeated local rivals [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Independiente|Independiente]] 2\u20130 in the [[Avellaneda derby]] at  [[Estadio Presidente Juan Domingo Per\u00f3n|Estadio Juan Domingo Per\u00f3n]].<ref>[http://www.buenosairesherald.com/article/109282/racing-beat-independiente-20 \"Racing beat Independiente 2-0 (match report)\"]. ''Buenos Aires Herald'', 20 August 2012. Retrieved 25 January 2013.</ref> This performance was considered the youngster's breakthrough game for ''La Academia'', and he went on to establish himself as the squad's first-choice [[Midfielder#Wide midfielder|left midfielder]] in a [[Formation (association football)#4\u20134\u20132|4\u20134\u20132 formation]].<ref>[http://www.football-lineups.com/footballer/71387/?t=961&s=170 \"Adri\u00e1n Ricardo Centuri\u00f3n appearance stats, Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n 2012/13\"]. ''Football-Lineups.com''. Retrieved 25 January 2013.</ref>\n\nRacing president Gast\u00f3n Cogorno confirmed on 24 January 2013 that Centuri\u00f3n was on the verge of agreeing a deal to join [[Russian Football Premier League|Russian top division]] outfit [[FC Anzhi Makhachkala|Anzhi Makhachkala]] in the summer of 2013.<ref>[http://www.goal.com/en/news/585/argentina/2013/01/22/3692802/ricardo-centurion-set-for-summer-anzhi-switch \"Ricardo Centurion set for summer Anzhi switch\"]. ''Goal.com'', 22 January 2013. Retrieved 25 January 2013.</ref> During negotiations, the deal fell through after contract disagreements between the two clubs.\n\nOn 2 September 2013, the final day of the summer transfer window, Italian club [[Genoa C.F.C.|Genoa]] confirmed the signing of Centuri\u00f3n on a season long loan with an option to buy at the end of the [[2013\u201314 Serie A|2013\u201314 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11854/8903468/|title=Transfer Deadline Day: Genoa sign Argentinian winger Ricardo Centurion on loan|publisher=SkySports.com|author=Nadia Carminati|date=2 September 2013|accessdate=24 July 2017}}</ref> He endured a difficult season in Italy, however, totaling only 12 appearances for club in Serie A, who ultimately decided not to trigger the purchase clause at the end of the season, resulting in his return to Racing the following summer.<ref name=\"caso Centurion\">{{cite web |url=https://www.foxsports.it/2017/11/03/serie-a-genoa-caso-centurion-ritiro/ |title=Serie A, al Genoa c'\u00e8 il caso Centurion: l'argentino non va in ritiro |trans-title=Serie A, at Genoa there is the Centuri\u00f3n case: the Argentine is not going to the team's training camp |publisher=Fox Sports |language=Italian |last1=Minuti |first1=Daniele |date=3 November 2011 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\n===S\u00e3o Paulo and loan with Boca Juniors===\nOn 30 January 2015, it was confirmed that Centuri\u00f3n signed for Brazilian club [[S\u00e3o Paulo FC]], who gained 70% of the player's rights for \u20ac4.2 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Sao-paulo-achete-centurion/532596|title=S\u00e3o Paulo ach\u00e8te Centurion|trans-title=S\u00e3o Paulo buys Centuri\u00f3n|work=L'\u00c9quipe|language=French|date=30 January 2015|accessdate=24 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Centuri\u00f3n returned to Argentina, in a season-long loan deal with [[Boca Juniors]], with the option to be fully signed by the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/times/sao-paulo/noticia/2016/08/sao-paulo-acerta-emprestimo-de-centurion-para-o-boca-juniors.html|title=S\u00e3o Paulo acerta empr\u00e9stimo de Centuri\u00f3n para o Boca Juniors|trans-title=S\u00e3o Paulo confirms Centuri\u00f3n's loan to Boca Juniors|publisher=GloboEsporte.Globo.com|language=Portuguese|date=9 August 2016|accessdate=24 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.us/story/3107332/boca-juniors-target-summer-buy-back-from-shanghai-shenhua-for-carlos-tevez|title=Boca Juniors target summer Shanghai Shenhua buy-back for Carlos Tevez|publisher=ESPN FC|date=19 April 2017|accessdate=24 July 2017}}</ref> He was awarded the [[Squad number (association football)|number 10 shirt]], which had previously also been worn by [[Carlos Tevez]] and [[Diego Maradona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eldiario24.com/nota/deportes/392473/10-boca-juniors-ya-tiene-nombre-apellido-ricardo-centurion.html|title=La 10 de Boca Juniors ya tiene nombre y apellido: Ricardo Centuri\u00f3n|trans-title=The 10 of Boca Juniors already has a name and surname: Ricardo Centuri\u00f3n|publisher=ElDiario24.com|language=Spanish|date=24 January 2017|accessdate=24 July 2017}}</ref> Despite some initial disciplinary issues off the pitch, he later played a decisive role in helping his club to win the [[2016\u201317 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n]] title.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.us/blog/espn-fc-united-blog/68/post/3150225/five-reasons-why-boca-juniors-are-champions-of-argentina-again|title=Five reasons why Boca Juniors are champions of Argentina again|publisher=ESPN FC|author=Sam Kelly|date=29 June 2017|accessdate=24 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Second spells at Genoa and Racing and further loan spells===\nIn the summer of 2017, Centuri\u00f3n signed with Italian club Genoa for the second time.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calciomercato/29-07-2017/genoa-centurion-talento-boca-juniors-roberto-baggio-210619052189.shtml |title=Genoa, torna Centurion: talento e follia per l'ex Boca Juniors che piace a Baggio |trans-title=Genoa, Centuri\u00f3n returns: talent and folly for the former Boca Juniors player whom Baggio likes |work=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=Italian |last1=Da Ronch |first1=Alessio |date=29 July 217 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref> He once again had a difficult experience with the team, making only three league appearances for the club, and two in the Coppa Italia, before being sold to Racing Club once again in January 2018, for \u20ac6 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/it/notizie/calciomercato-genoa-secondo-addio-a-centurion-va-al-racing/18mkzxqok67xr1q6nz7wj9tq6s |title=Calciomercato Genoa, secondo addio a Centurion: va al Racing Avellaneda per 6M |trans-title=Genoa transfer news, Centuri\u00f3n's second goodbye: he is going to Racing Avellaneda for \u20ac6 million |publisher=Goal.com |language=Italian |date=18 January 2018 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\nAfter arguing with Racing's manager during a match, and being left out of the squad as a result,<ref name=\"gender-based violence clause\"/> in June 2019, Centuri\u00f3n was loaned out to Mexican side [[Atl\u00e9tico San Luis]];<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.foxsports.com.ar/news/158784-oscar-el-mejor-jugador-de-brasil-en-el-debut,ar/news/410994-centurion-ya-es-jugador-del-atletico-san-luis |title=Centuri\u00f3n ya es jugador del Atl\u00e9tico San Luis |trans-title=Centuri\u00f3n is already a player of Atl\u00e9tico San Luis |publisher=Fox Sports |language=Spanish |date=8 June 2019 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref> however, after a difficult first part of the season and a lack of playing time, he asked to leave the club and return to Argentina in November.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://mexico.as.com/mexico/2019/11/15/futbol/1573793130_541786.html |title=Ricardo Centuri\u00f3n no continuar\u00e1 en el Atl\u00e9tico de San Luis |trans-title=Ricardo Centuri\u00f3n will not continue with Atl\u00e9rico de San Luis |publisher=mexico.as.com |language=Spanish |last1=Sena |first1=Guadalupe |date=14 November 2019 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\nIn January 2020, he was sent on loan to [[Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield|V\u00e9lez Sarsfield]] for the remainder of the 2019\u201320 season, who inserted a clause into his contract stating that it would be terminated if he were to be accused of gender violence.<ref name=\"gender-based violence clause\">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/jan/24/boca-velez-centurion-clause-gender-violence-argentina-football |title=Will a clause against gender-based violence change Argentinian football? |work=The Guardian |last1=Navas |first1=Francisco |date=24 January 2020 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nAt international youth level, Centuri\u00f3n was a member of the [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina U20 squad]] that took part at the [[2013 South American Youth Football Championship]]; he made three apperances throughout the tournament, as the nation suffered a first\u2013round elimination.<ref name=\"SW\"/><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/deportes/futbol/papelon-y-fracaso-el-sub-20-eliminado-del-sudamericano-en-primera-rueda-nid1545972 |title=Un fracaso: el Sub 20, eliminado en primera rueda y afuera del Mundial |trans-title=A failure: the under-20, eliminated in the first round and out of the World Cup |work=La Nacion |language=Spanish |date=17 January 2013 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\nIn May 2018, he was named in [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]]'s preliminary 35 man [[Argentina national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia by manager [[Jorge Sampaoli]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/amp/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad - Final 23-man lists|publisher=Goal.com|last=Crawford|first=Stephen|date=4 June 2018|accessdate=4 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/icardi-cut-from-argentinas-23-man-world-cup-squad/lo0f6fig55ih1jh7w9v4enau6 |title=Icardi cut from Argentina's 23-man World Cup squad |website=[[Goal (website)|Goal.com]] |publisher=[[Perform Group]] |date=21 May 2018 |access-date=21 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Style of play==\nIn 2013, Centuri\u00f3n was described by the ''[[BBC]]'' as a \"whippy, quick, skilful [[support striker]] whose elusive [[Dribbling#Association football|dribbling]] made a big impact in the recent Argentine championship\".<ref name=\"bbc\">[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/20521275 \"January 2013 transfer window: Top 50 players who could move\"]. ''BBC Sport'', 7 January 2013. Retrieved 25 January 2013.</ref> His dribbling ability often leads him to undertake individual runs, or pull off elaborate [[Dummy (football)|feints]] and moves in one on one situations, in order to challenge or beat opponents, such as the [[step over]].<ref name=\"gender-based violence clause\"/><ref name=\"new Di Maria\"/> His style of play drew early comparisons to compatriot [[\u00c1ngel Di Mar\u00eda]] in the media.<ref name=\"vivaformica\"/><ref name=\"new Di Maria\">{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/blog/name/93/post/1853496/headline |title=Portuguese giants fight over 'new Di Maria' |publisher=ESPN FC |last1=Atkins |first1=Christopher |date=20 December 2012 |accessdate=31 March 2020 }}</ref><ref name=\"introducing Ricky Centuri\u00f3n\">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/blog/2012/sep/04/ricky-centurion-guardian-sport-network |title=He plays like Di Mar\u00eda and dances like Tevez: introducing Ricky Centuri\u00f3n |work=The Guardian |last1=Edwards |first1=Dan |date=4 September 2012 |accessdate=31 March 2020 }}</ref> In 2012, ''Viva Formica'' described the [[playmaker]] with the following words: \"Quick footed and quick witted, the ambidextrous winger is confident standing up to a marker. His tricky style and technical nous allows him to beat a man repeatedly whilst can still [[Cross (football)|deliver a decent ball]].\"<ref name=\"vivaformica\">[http://vivaformica.wordpress.com/2012/11/13/barcelona-eye-racing-starlet-centurion/ \"Barcelona eye Racing starlet Centurion\"]. ''Viva Formica'', 13 November 2012. Retrieved 25 January 2013.</ref> That same year, Christopher Atkins of ''[[ESPN FC]]'' described him as: \"Comfortable with the ball on either side, fleet of foot and able to change direction at a moment's notice, there have been few defenders in the Primera Division able to live with his abilities this year. The one frustration is that the youngster can attempt to overplay, when the easier option may suffice.\" He also cited the youngster's decision\u2013making as another aspect of his game in need of improvement.<ref name=\"new Di Maria\"/> In addition to highlighting Centuri\u00f3n's pace, technical skills, and excellent right foot, Matteo Macor of ''[[La Repubblica]]'' also noted in 2017 that the Argentine possesses good vision.<ref name=\"repubblica\">{{cite news |url=https://genova.repubblica.it/cronaca/2017/07/29/news/genoa-171871893/ |title=Genoa, benedetto da Baggio come possibile erede: Centurion firma e ora pu\u00f2 far sognare |trans-title=Genoa, blessed by Baggio as his possible heir: Centuri\u00f3n signs and now he can make others dream |work=La Repubblica |language=Italian |last1=Macor |first1=Matteo |date=29 July 2017 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref> \n\nCenturi\u00f3n's favoured role is either as a [[Midfielder#Wide midfielder|wide midfielder]], or as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] or [[Forward (association football)#Winger|outside forward]] on the left flank, a position which allows him to cut inside and strike on goal with his stronger right foot.<ref name=\"blastingnews\">{{cite web |url=https://it.blastingnews.com/calcio/2017/07/calciomercato-genoa-arriva-centurion-lerede-di-roberto-baggio-001882551.html |title=Calciomercato Genoa: arriva Centurion, l'erede di Roberto Baggio |trans-title=Genoa transfer\u2013news: Centuri\u00f3n is arriving, the heir of Roberto Baggio |publisher=it.blastingnews.com |language=Italian |last1=Zanichelli |first1=Matteo |date=27 July 2017 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref> Regarded by pundits as a highly promising yet undisciplined player, due to his turbulent and controversial lifestyle off the pitch, in a 2017 interview with ''La Repubblica'', Italian former playmaker [[Roberto Baggio]] described Centuri\u00f3n as his potential \"heir\" and as the player whose characteristics currently most resembled his own playing style, with the Italian commenting: \"...I really like Centuri\u00f3n, but he has to improve his behaviour off the pitch.\"<ref name=\"repubblica\"/><ref name=\"goal.com\">{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/who-is-ricardo-centurion-the-boca-juniors-star-roberto/139ht5wdl0o3c1eaa46eu9h707 |title=Who is Ricardo Centurion? The nightclub fighting star Roberto Baggio labelled as his heir |publisher=Goal.com |last1=Edwards |first1=Daniel |date=25 July 2017 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.football-italia.net/106237/baggio-my-heir-penalty-hell |title=Baggio: My heir & penalty hell... |publisher=Football Italia |date=24 July 2017 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref> Despite his talent, and the praise that he earned in the Italian media for his creativity, as well as his explosive and unpredictable dribbling,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://zonacesarini.net/2017/08/03/ricardo-centurion-il-ritorno-del-wachiturro/ |title=RICARDO CENTURI\u00d3N, IL RITORNO DEL WACHITURRO |trans-title=Ricardo Centuri\u00f3n, the Return of the Wachiturro |publisher=Zona Cesarini |language=Italian |last1=Madera |first1=Andrea |date=3 August 2017 |accessdate=31 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telegenova.net/articolo.php?id=996 |title=Genoa, finalmente Centurion. Paletta e Ranocchia nel mirino |trans-title=Genoa, finally Centuri\u00f3n. Paletta and Ranocchia in their sight |publisher=Tele Genova |language=Italian |last1=Bacci |first1=Alessandro |date=28 July 2017 |accessdate=31 March 2020 }}</ref> he also drew criticism over his disappointing performances and poor positional sense on the pitch during his time in Serie A.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/serie-a/centurion-e-l-eredita-di-roberto-baggio-totalmente-fuori-contesto-1019828 |title=Centurion e l'eredit\u00e0 di Roberto Baggio. Totalmente fuori contesto |trans-title=Centurion and the heredity of Roberto Baggio. Completely out of context. |publisher=www.tuttomercatoweb.com |language=Italian |last1=Conterio |first1=Marco |date=18 September 2017 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref> Italian journalist Gianluca Sartori highlighted the contrast, noting that while Centuri\u00f3n was a highly talented young player, gifted with an incredible change of pace, technique, the ability to get past his opponents, and the capacity to attack from either side of the pitch, he also had an immature character, a poor mentality, and a low work-rate, which is why he believed that the Argentine winger struggled to adapt to the more physical and tactical brand of football played in Italy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.toronews.net/campionato/genoa-centurion-e-in-cerca-di-riscatto/ |title=Genoa, con Centurion ti \u00e8 andata male? |trans-title=Genoa, did things go badly for you with Centuri\u00f3n? |publisher=Toro News |language=Italian |last1=Sartori |first1=Gianluca |date=10 April 2014 |accessdate=31 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\nAfter scoring a goal, Centuri\u00f3n has been known to incorporate dance moves into his [[goal celebration]]s, which has led him to be compared to compatriot Carlos Tevez in the media.<ref name=\"introducing Ricky Centuri\u00f3n\"/>\n\n==Controversy==\nCenturi\u00f3n has drawn widespread criticism in the media for his behaviour and lack of discipline, and has been involved in a number of highly controversial and publicised incidents off the pitch. In a 2017 article for ''[[Goal.com]]'', Daniel Edwards noted that \"in the last 12 months alone Centurion [sic] has been accused of walking away from a [[Traffic collision|traffic incident]] caused [[Driving under the influence|driving while drunk]], and fighting in hotels and in the dark streets of an Avellaneda shanty town in the early hours of the morning. More seriously, the 24-year-old faces [[domestic violence]] charges laid down by an ex-girlfriend, who alleges she was physically and emotionally abused during their time together.\"<ref name=\"goal.com\"/> \n\nMoreover, in 2017, during Centuri\u00f3n's negotiations with Boca to make his loan deal permanent, the winger gained further notoriety after he was involved in an altercation in a nightclub in Buenos Aires, which led one of the victims to file a police report against him; in an interview with Argentine sports newspaper ''[[Ol\u00e9 (sports newspaper)|Ol\u00e9]]'' the following week, Fabi\u00e1n Comande, one of the members of the group that was [[Assault|assaulted]] by Centuri\u00f3n and his entourage, after the latter had asked the player for a photo, commented: \"Centu [Centuri\u00f3n] threatened me with death, but on the pitch he is a star and very important for the team. [...] I hope he stays, and that this does not affect the negotiations.\"<ref name=\"blastingnews\"/><ref name=\"goal.com\"/><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ole.com.ar/boca-juniors/centurion-pase-conducta_0_Hk4t6sNL-.html |title=\u201cMe amenaz\u00f3 de muerte, pero quiero que se quede\u201d |trans-title=\"He threatened me with death, but I hope he stays |work=Ol\u00e9 |language=Spanish |date=25 July 2017 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\nFollowing Centuri\u00f3n's loan to V\u00e9lez Sarsfield in 2020, Francisco Navas of ''[[The Guardian]]'' summarised and commented on the [[midfielder]]'s history of scandalous behaviour off the pitch, stating: \"Since turning professional with Racing Club in 2012, the 27-year-old has had three of his professional contracts rescinded for his behavior. Among other things, he has fallen out of favor for partying too much; been photographed in his swimming trunks while holding a [[shotgun]];<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.infobae.com/deportes-2/2017/07/10/otro-escandalo-para-ricardo-centurion-aparecio-una-nueva-foto-suya-con-un-arma/ |title=Otro esc\u00e1ndalo para Centuri\u00f3n: apareci\u00f3 una nueva foto suya con un arma |trans-title=Another scandal for Centuri\u00f3n: a new photo of his with a firearm has appeared |work=infobae |language=Spanish |date=10 July 2017 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref> insulted the [[Daniel Angelici|president of Boca Juniors [Daniel Angelici];]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://espectaculos.clarin.com/deportes/futbol/boca-juniors/angelici-dijo-centurion-canso-apuro-reemplazarlo_0_B1w8G2I8b.html |title=Angelici dijo que Centuri\u00f3n lo cans\u00f3 y que no tiene apuro por reemplazarlo |trans-title=Angelici said that Centuri\u00f3n tired him and that he is in no hurry to replace him |publisher=Clar\u00edn |language=Spanish |last1=Avellaneda |first1=Daniel |date=26 July 2017 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref> tried to [[Bribery|bribe]] a [[police officer]] to avoid a [[Breathalyzer|drink-driving test]];<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/deportes/futbol/nuevo-escandalo-ricardo-centurion-se-nego-a-un-control-de-alcoholemia-e-intento-sobornar-a-un-policia-nid2118283 |title=Otro esc\u00e1ndalo de Ricardo Centuri\u00f3n: intent\u00f3 sobornar a un polic\u00eda tras negarse a un control de alcoholemia |trans-title=Another Ricardo Centuri\u00f3n scandal: he tried to bribe a police officer after refusing to undergo a brethalyser test |work=La Nacion |language=Spanish |date=19 March 2018 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref> crashed his car while trying to evade police;<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.clarin.com/deportes/futbol/boca-juniors/jugador-Boca-envuelto-confuso-accidente_0_H12cg1is.html |title=Centuri\u00f3n admiti\u00f3 ser el conductor del BMW en el choque y fue imputado |trans-title=Centuri\u00f3n admitted to being the driver of the BMW in the collision and was arrested |work=El Clar\u00edn |language=Spanish |date=5 September 2016 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref> fought his own teammates;<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.infobae.com/deportes-2/2017/02/15/nuevo-escandalo-en-boca-difunden-un-polemico-video-de-centurion/ |title=Nuevo esc\u00e1ndalo en Boca: difunden un pol\u00e9mico video de Centuri\u00f3n |trans-title=New scandal at Boca: they shared a controversial video of Centuri\u00f3n |work=infobae |language=Spanish |date=15 February 2017 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref> and argued with his manager mid-game.\"<ref name=\"gender-based violence clause\"/> \n\nNavas also noted that the club introduced a clause into his contract, giving them permission to cancel the contract if he were to be accused of gender violence, given the past accusations he had faced; the journalist further expanded on the latter incident, stating: \"In 2013, his then-girlfriend, Melisa Tozzi, accused him of beating her, breaking three of her teeth and giving her two black eyes in the process.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.infobae.com/deportes-2/2017/05/24/me-astillo-tres-dientes-y-me-ahorco-el-relato-de-la-ex-novia-de-centurion/ |title=\"Me astill\u00f3 tres dientes y me ahorc\u00f3\": el relato de la ex novia de Centuri\u00f3n |trans-title=\"He shattered three of my teeth and hanged me\": the story of the former girlfriend of Centuri\u00f3n |work=infobae |language=Spanish |date=24 May 2017 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref> During a TV interview, she shared messages from Centuri\u00f2n in which he appeared to check up on her injuries. 'Let\u2019s not let this happen again,' he wrote to her on [[Facebook]].\"<ref name=\"gender-based violence clause\"/>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn a 2018 interview on an Argentine television show ''PH, podemos hablar'', Centuri\u00f3n spoke of his personal life, including his love of [[weapon]]s and [[firearm]]s, as well as the fact that he used to consume [[Cannabis (drug)|cannabis]] when he first started out playing professional football. He also spoke of his difficult childhood, commenting that his father had died in an explosion while working in an illegal firework factory, when Ricardo was only five, and that he no longer has any memories of him as a result; he also revealed that he is currently unable to return to his hometown, which has led to personal strains within his family.<ref name=\"confessa\"/> \n\nCenturi\u00f3n's nickname is \"El Wachiturro,\" due to his fashion style, \"[[gaucho]]\" heritage, and love of [[cumbia]] music, specifically the Argentine cumbia teen boyband \"Los Wachiturros,\" of whom he is a fan, and whose members he is thought to resemble in terms of his physical appearance.<ref name=\"introducing Ricky Centuri\u00f3n\"/><ref name=\"confessa\">{{cite news |url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Estero/29-07-2018/centurion-genoa-armi-droga-racing-2801003062505.shtml |title=Centurion, ex Genoa, si confessa: \u201cAmo le armi e ho fatto uso di droghe\u201d |trans-title=Centuri\u00f3n, a former Genoa player, confesses: \"I love firearms and I have used drugs\" |work=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=Italian |last1=Saetta |first1=Giulio |date=29 July 2018 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/1718706-why-juventus-target-ricardo-centurion-is-argentinas-new-di-maria |title=Why Juventus Target Ricardo Centurion Is Argentina's New Di Maria |publisher=Bleacher Report |last1=Colasimone |first1=Dan |date=27 July 2013 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/es-cl/news/4778/main/2016/09/13/27471022/centuri%C3%B3n-de-la-televisi%C3%B3n-a-la-cancha |title=Centuri\u00f3n: de la televisi\u00f3n a la cancha |trans-title=Centuri\u00f3n: from television to the pitch |publisher=Goal.com |last1=Scher |first1=Ezequiel |language=Spanish |date=13 September 2016 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://forzaitalianfootball.com/2013/07/roma-and-napoli-target-argentine-midfielder/amp/ |title=Roma and Napoli Target Argentine Midfielder |publisher=forzaitalianfootball.com |last1=Doria |first1=Vito |date=3 July 2013 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref> He has also often been referred to in the media by the nickname \"Ricky.\"<ref name=\"new Di Maria\"/><ref name=\"introducing Ricky Centuri\u00f3n\"/>\n\nCenturi\u00f3n's girlfriend, Melody Pasini, died in a road accident on 29 March 2020; according to news reports in Argentina, she suffered a [[Cardiac arrest|heart attack]] while she was driving and lost control of her vehicle.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.football-italia.net/151632/ex-genoa-man-suffers-tragedy |title=Ex-Genoa man suffers tragedy |publisher=Football Italia |date=29 March 2020 |accessdate=30 March 2020 }}</ref> Centuri\u00f3n addressed the news on social media later that day, with an [[Instagram]] post that included a photo of himself with his girlfriend, and the underlying caption: \"I will always love you my love.\"<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/america/20200330/48180575383/la-dolorosa-despedida-de-centurion-a-su-novia.html |title=La dolorosa despedida de Centuri\u00f3n a su novia |trans-title=Centuri\u00f3n's painful farewell to his girlfriend |work=Mundo Deportivo |language=Spanish |date=30 March 2020 |accessdate=31 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 14 March 2020}}<ref name=\"SW\">{{cite web|title=R. Centuri\u00f3n|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/adrian-ricardo-centurion/248168/|website=Soccerway|accessdate=18 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n